The paper discusses the use of machine learning and simulation software for developing and testing autonomous driving software, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence and robotics. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of photorealistic simulation, which involves computer vision techniques, making cs.CV a likely sub-category as well. The use of machine learning models for processing data from virtual sensors and controlling vehicles falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the monitoring and evaluation of the performance of the hybrid simulator, which falls under the category of control systems, making cs.SY a possible sub-category.
